In a large saucepan, over medium heat, sauté pumpkin flowers and onion in 1 tablespoon margarine; when onion is translucent add 2 cups milk; lower heat and simmer for 3 minutes. Puree onion, flowers, and milk mixture in blender. In the same saucepan, melt the remaining 1 tablespoon margarine; stir flour into margarine until a thick paste is formed; continue stirring; gradually add flower mixture. When soup thickens stir in consommé, zucchini, corn, and remaining 2 cups milk; simmer for 10 minutes over low heat; stir occasionally. Season with pepper.